    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Note that \"Westwood PALs\" are standard [VGA color palettes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Video_Graphics_Array#Color_palette), and not special/proprietary to Westwood in any way.\r\n\r\nAlpha/Normal/Depth channels become simple shader details once we move to an OpenGL >= 3 based renderer using [array textures](https://www.khronos.org/opengl/wiki/Array_Texture) instead of limiting ourselves to 4 channels per texture.  That brings many other performance and sanity benefits, but requires raising our minimum hardware requirements."
  },
